******
[4] Finland ex Germany
Date: Fri 3 Jun 2011
Source: Xinhua News Agency [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english2010/world/2011-06/03/c_13910189.htm


A case of the _E. coli_ (EHEC) bacterial infection has been diagnosed
in Helsinki, the Finnish National Institute for Health and Welfare
said Fri 3 Jun 2011.

The properties of the _E. coli_ bacterium found in the patient are
similar to those exhibited by the deadly bacteria in Germany. The
patient has been in Germany recently and is now recovering, the
institute said.

